cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper discusses recent advances in machine reading comprehension, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This sub-category covers topics related to natural language processing, which is a key component of machine reading comprehension. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are also essential for MRC. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category covers topics related to machine learning, which is a core technique used in MRC. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): This sub-category covers topics related to information retrieval, which is closely related to MRC as both involve understanding and extracting information from text. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This sub-category covers topics related to neural networks, which are commonly used in MRC techniques.
